Pre-heat your #oven{} to 220 degrees and boil a #pot{} of water. Rub @olive oil{1/4%tsp} on each @British Chicken Thighs{6} along with a good pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Coat thoroughly in your @BBQ Sauce{4%tbsp}. Place them on a #baking tray{} and cook them in the oven on the top shelf for ~{25%minutes} until the skin is nice and crispy.

> Take the chicken out of the oven halfway through to recoat with the BBQ sauce and fat that has dripped to the side, to keep it nice and moist.

Chop the @New Potatoes{1} in half. Finely chop the @Coriander{5%sprigs}(finely chopped) and slice the @Spring Onion{3} into thin discs. Remove the core from the @Red Pepper{1} and finely chop into ½cm cubes.

Drain and thoroughly rinse your @Organic Black Beans{2} and @Organic Sweetcorn{1}, then leave them to drip dry in a #colander{} until later.

Add @salt{1/4%tsp} to the boiling water and gently plop in your potatoes. Cook them for around ~{10%minutes} or until you can easily slip a knife through them. Drain and keep to the side.

Roll the @Lime{1} firmly between your palm and your #chopping board{} until it loosens up. Grate a pinch of lime zest into a #small bowl{} and squeeze in half of its juice. Mix thoroughly with the @Sour Cream{1%tbsp}, @olive oil{2%tbsp} and @salt{1/4%tsp}.

Mix the black beans with the sweetcorn and the finely chopped red pepper. Chop the cooked new potatoes in half again and add these to the mix. Finally add in the spring onion.

Once the chicken is cooked (i.e. it is no longer pink in the middle) remove from the oven. Leave the chicken to rest for ~{5%minutes} and finely chop it into 1cm cubes.

> Chopping the meat like this will spread its flavour more evenly through the dish.

Add the chicken and three quarters of the coriander into the bean mixture. Pour over your sour cream dressing and gently toss together.

> We recommend using clean fingertips to gently toss the ingredients.

Sprinkle over the remaining coriander, squeeze in more lime juice and get stuck in.

> Pour over the remaining juices from your chicken tray for a little extra flavour!